result.execSummary:
The defendant Micayla M. Palmer was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Micayla M. Palmer is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Micayla M. Palmer was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse - Threat], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Micayla M. Palmer in court with attorney Brian F. Bennett.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court calls 15CM60, 14CM183, 14CM187 & 14CM202 @ 9:20 am.  State gives plea agreement 15CM60 ct 1 plea ct 2 dismissed w/o prejudice, costs only on ct 1. 14CM202 Expungement deny, 14CM187, Has not fulfilled all terms but is dismissing w/o prejudice, 14CM183 Dismiss. All victims rights complied with on all 4 files.  Atty Bennett & def. agree with plea agreement. 15CM60 Plea questionnaire & waiver of rights filed.  Def. understands charge & penalties.  Ct 1 in 15CM60, no contest plea. Ct 2 Dismissed w/o prejudice.  Def. advised of constitutional rights & J.T. rights. Def. understands elements.  Atty Bennett is satisfied.  Court finds plea is freely & voluntarily given. Stipulate to factual basis.  Court finds factual basis, accepts plea & finds def. Guilty to D.C. Domestic, 947.01(1). State gives sentencing statement.  Atty Bennett gives sentencing statement.  Def. has nothing.  Court orders on ct 1 costs only, DNA sample & 200. surcharge. Def given p.p. Def. advised of postconviction rights. 
14CM183 Ct 1 Dismiss, Terms have not been complied, however, dismiss w/prejudice & 14CM187 Ct 1 Dismiss w/ prejudice. 14CM202 Expungement Denied.
